# DMIT backend (applies to apps/dmit-api only)

DMIT is the only place server-only secrets live. It is also the only writer
to `usage_logs`, `credit_ledger`, `profiles`, and `api_keys`.

## Auth scheme per endpoint

| Endpoint | Auth | Verifier |
|---|---|---|
| `GET/POST/DELETE /v1/keys` | `Bearer <supabase_access_token>` | `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` (HS256, jose) |
| `POST /v1/billing/checkout` | `Bearer <supabase_access_token>` | same |
| `POST /v1/chat/completions` | `Bearer sk-tokfai_<hex>` | lookup by `key_id`, compare `HMAC-SHA256(TOKEN_PEPPER, secret)` constant-time |
| `GET  /v1/models` | `Bearer sk-tokfai_...` | same |
| `POST /v1/webhooks/stripe` | `Stripe-Signature` header | `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` |
| `GET  /v1/health` | none | — |

## Write rules

- Writes to `profiles.credits_balance`, `total_credits_purchased`,
  `total_credits_used` MUST go through the Postgres RPCs
  (`public.debit_credits`, `public.credit_purchase`) — they enforce
  atomicity and idempotency.
- Direct `update profiles set credits_balance = ...` from application code is
  forbidden. Always RPC.
- `usage_logs` insert is the only place we record per-request data. One
  insert per request, even for failures (with `status != 'succeeded'`).
- Never UPDATE an existing `usage_logs` row to change billing data after the
  fact — write a `credit_ledger` `adjustment` row instead, so the history
  stays auditable.

## API key format

```
sk-tokfai_<48 lowercase hex chars>
```

- random part = 24 random bytes encoded as lowercase hex
- `key_id` = first 12 chars of the random hex, used for indexed lookup
- Stored: `key_id` (indexed), `prefix = secret.slice(0, 18) + "..."`,
  `hash = HMAC-SHA256(TOKEN_PEPPER, secret)` hex
- Lookup by `key_id` is O(1) via the partial unique index where
  `revoked_at IS NULL`
- Compare must use `crypto.timingSafeEqual`

## Error envelope (OpenAI-style)

Every non-2xx response body:

```json
{ "error": { "message": "...", "code": "...", "type": "..." } }
```

`code` and `type` are stable enums consumed by frontend UIs.

## What NOT to do

- ❌ Don't read `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars here. DMIT is server-only.
- ❌ Don't import anything from `apps/web`. The two apps are decoupled.
- ❌ Don't log API keys, JWTs, or Stripe webhook bodies in full. Log the
  `key_id` / `request_id` / Stripe `event.id` only.
- ❌ Don't use the Supabase anon key. Use service_role only.
- ❌ Don't store the raw `sk-tokfai_...` secret anywhere — only the HMAC hash.
